Starting on the 10th, he had two birdies in his first six holes. As the names that usually clutter the top of the first-day leaderboard of a PGA did their thing, Woods was right there at the turn, his putter, the tool that did him in at the British Open, rock-solid, being used just 11 times as he saved par after par.
